-- Chevron Is Only Bidder for Lithuania Shale-Gas Rights, BNS Says
-- B y   B r y a n   B r a d l e y
-- 2013-01-15T10:46:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/chevron-is-only-bidder-for-lithuania-shale-gas-rights-bns-says.html
Chevron Exploration and Production
Lietuva, a Lithuanian subsidiary of  Chevron Corp. (CVX) , submitted the
only bid in a tender for shale-gas exploration rights in the
Baltic nation, Baltic News Service reported.  If the bid is accepted, the company would need to invest at
least 80 million litai ($31 million) in exploration of the
Silute-Taurage field in western Lithuania, the newswire said,
citing the head of the geological service, Juozas Mockevicius.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Bradley in Vilnius at 
 bbradley13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  